FBIS3-28593 "dreas026__a94014" FBIS-EAS-94-026-A Document Type:Daily Report 8 February 1994 ANNEX Japan DA Chief Objects to Opposition to AWACS OW0302121894 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 3 Feb 94 Morning Edition p 7 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW0302121894 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN Language: Japanese Article Type:BFN [Text] On 2 February Kazuo Aichi, director general of the Defense Agency, objected to opposition voiced by Tomiichi Murayama, chairman of the Social Democratic Party of Japan [SDPJ], against a plan to appropriate funds in the draft budget for the next fiscal year for the procurement of Airborne Warning and Control System (AWACS) aircraft. He was speaking at a news conference held the same day at Hyakuri Air Self-Defense Force Base. Aichi stated: "The coalition government started off after confirming it would inherit the basic policies of the previous administration regarding national security and diplomacy. It is my understanding that the plan to purchase AWACS aircraft is a part of these policies."
